Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop onto a
large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}
then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @Red Leicester{30%grams}.

Pop the @Unconventional Plant-Based Burgers{2} onto a lightly oiled baking tray.
When the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf until cooked through,
~{6-7%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure they're piping hot throughout.

Meanwhile, chop the @medium tomato{1} into 2cm chunks.

Put the @cider vinegar{15%ml}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the
dressing into a #medium bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Mix together and add the tomato chunks. Stir to combine and set aside.

Once the burgers have cooked, carefully place the cheese on top of the burgers
and pop back into the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @burger buns{2}. Pop onto a baking tray and into your oven
to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, spread the @BBQ sauce{32%grams} over the bun bases.

Top the bases with the burgers and a handful of @baby leaf mix{20%grams}, then
sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Add the remaining baby leaves to your bowl of dressing and toss to coat.

Serve your plant-based burgers with the wedges and salad alongside. Enjoy!